annotationA: TBP-associated factor 13; Protein heterodimerization activity; RNA polymerase II core promoter sequence-specific DNA binding transcription factor activity involved in preinitiation complex assembly. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
annotationB: ENL/AF9-related, isoform A; ENL/AF9-related is a transcription factor that is a component of the super elongation complex (SEC), which regulates transcription by RNA Polymerase II. It also interacts with the histone methyltransferase gpp in the Dot1 complex (DotCom), which modifies chromatin structure by methylating histone H3 on lysine 79
